Description: Large blue glazed composition jar with circular foot, drop-shaped body and everted rim, exterior worn, whole reconstructed from fragments.
Curator's comments: Published: H. Coutts, Gold of the Pharaohs, Edinburgh 1988, pp. 92-93 [68/A]. Brissaud and Zivie-Coche - Tanis 1987-1997, (1998). pgs175, 130. [pl.29].
